    <stitle>BRAKE COMPONENTS: This Service Manual Section should be used for reference only. For more current service
        information on all components go to the Bendix website from the ISIS Suppliers menu and refer to the Service
        Data Sheets. - TWO WAY CONTROL VALVE (BENDIX TYPE TW-1) - DISASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s04002r_81.xml" xrefid="f0400238">Figure 38</hotlnk>
            for all items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press out lever roll pin.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If valve is of the push-pull type, loosen jam nut at control button, then remove button and
                jam nut.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove plunger (Item 6) and plunger return spring (Item 3) from body.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unscrew cap nut at inlet port and remove valve spring (Item 5) and valve from body.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove grommets from plunger (Item 6) and cap nut.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
